{"id":"1311.4956","submitter":"Alexander Seidel","authors":"Li Chen, Tahereh Mazaheri, Alexander Seidel, and Xiang Tang","title":"The impossibility of exactly flat non-trivial Chern bands in strictly\n  local periodic tight binding models","comments":"Published Version. Some references and additional comments added","journal-ref":"J. Phys. A: Math. Theor. 47 (2014) 152001","doi":"10.1088/1751-8113/47/15/152001","report-no":null,"categories":"cond-mat.str-el math-ph math.MP quant-ph","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We investigate the possibility of exactly flat non-trivial Chern bands in\ntight binding models with local (strictly short-ranged) hopping parameters. We\ndemonstrate that while any two of three criteria can be simultaneously realized\n(exactly flat band, non-zero Chern number, local hopping), it is not possible\nto simultaneously satisfy all three. Our theorem covers both the case of a\nsingle flat band, for which we give a rather elementary proof, as well as the\ncase of multiple degenerate flat bands. In the latter case, our result is\nobtained as an application of $K$-theory. We also introduce a class of models\non the Lieb lattice with nearest and next-nearest neighbor hopping parameters,\nwhich have an isolated exactly flat band of zero Chern number but, in general,\nnon-zero Berry curvature.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 20 Nov 2013 04:44:09 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 11 Apr 2014 16:59:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-04-14"}
